This paper is primarily focused on visual saliency prediction, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method also utilizes deep convolutional neural networks (DCNN), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of probability distribution prediction, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on several benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
